   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <hazardstatement type="danger" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">
                  <sl class="- topic/sl ">
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Electrical equipment must be installed, operated, serviced, and
maintained only by qualified personnel.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Apply appropriate personal protective equipment (PPE) and follow
safe electrical work practices.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Disconnection devices for AC and DC must be provided by others,
be readily accessible, and the function of the disconnect device marked
for its function.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Turn off the upstream disconnection devices.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Turn off all power supplying the UPS system before working on
or inside the equipment.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Before working on the UPS system, check for hazardous voltage
between all terminals including the protective earth.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">The UPS contains an internal energy source. Hazardous voltage
can be present even when disconnected from the mains supply. Before
installing or servicing the UPS system, ensure that the units are
OFF and that mains and batteries are disconnected. Wait five minutes
before opening the UPS to allow the capacitors to discharge.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">The UPS must be properly earthed/grounded and due to a high leakage
current, the earthing/grounding conductor must be connected first.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note class="- topic/note ">This procedure shows the 40
kVA UPS but the procedure is identical for all 10-40 kVA UPS systems.</note>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the screws of the front cover and remove the front
cover.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removefrontcover_w120mm_0000166133.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the cover in front of the leftmost fan.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removeinnercover_w120mm_0000166132.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Check that the connectors on the fan speed monitoring board
with the black and red wires are correctly labeled and disconnect
them.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the two screws from the fan speed monitoring board.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removemonitoringboard_w120mm_0000166131.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the two hex nuts on the fan assembly bracket and
remove the fan assembly bracket.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removefanbracket_w120mm_0000166130.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Slide the leftmost fan out and remove it as far as the
wires allow.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removeleftmostfan_w120mm_0000166129.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Move the other fans to the left and slide them out one
by one as far as the wires allow.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removelast3fans_w120mm_0000166128.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">From the new fan box, remove the fan speed monitoring board
and all four fans by sliding them out of the sheet metal frame. Discard
the sheet metal frame.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removefansandboardsfromnew_w120mm_0000166127.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Replace the old fans with the new fans one by one:</cmd>
            <substeps class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Disconnect the wires from the old fan.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Reconnect the wires to the new fan.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Slide the new fan into position in the fan holder.</cmd>
                  <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
                     <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                        <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_installnewfans_w120mm_0000166126.png"
                               placement="inline"
                               class="- topic/image "/>
                     </fig>
                  </stepxmp>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Reinstall the fan assembly bracket with the two hex nuts.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_reinstallfanbracket_w120mm_0000166125.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Replace the old fan speed monitoring board with the new
fan speed monitoring board:</cmd>
            <substeps class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Check that all the DIP switches on the new fan speed
monitoring board are set identically to the old fan speed monitoring
board.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Reconnect the connectors with the black and red wires
to the fan speed monitoring board.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Install the new fan speed monitoring board with the
two screws.</cmd>
                  <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
                     <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                        <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_installnewmonitoringboard_w120mm_0000166124.png"
                               placement="inline"
                               class="- topic/image "/>
                     </fig>
                  </stepxmp>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Reinstall the cover in front of the leftmost fan.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_re-installinnercover_w120mm_0000166143.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Reinstall the front cover with the screws.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
      <postreq class="- topic/section task/postreq ">Check the proper function of the fan assembly by closing
the Q001 breaker. Only the green LEDs on the fan speed monitoring
board must be on.</postreq>
